    <mj-section css-class="light-wrap" padding-bottom="20px" padding-top="20px">

      <mj-column>
        <mj-text font-size="28px" font-weight="bold" line-height="24px" padding-bottom="0">Fall 2025 Commencement</mj-text>
          <mj-text font-size="20px" font-weight="bold">Friday, December 19 | Lumberjack Arena</mj-text>
        <mj-image src="https://mailings.humboldt.edu/general/2025_12_05/grad_122024_01012_1.jpg" alt="Graduates posing for photo" />
        <mj-text>As we get ready to celebrate <a href="https://commencement.humboldt.edu">Fall Commencement</a>, the University is putting a few new safety measures in place to help the event run smoothly for everyone. Beginning this December, large campus events—including Commencement—will follow new clear bag guidelines and additional security measures.
          </mj-text>
        <mj-text><strong>Key Details:</strong>
          <ul>
<li>Bags larger than <strong>8.5” x 6” must be clear</strong> (transparent plastic, vinyl, or PVC). Small opaque wallets or clutches <strong>smaller</strong> than 8.5” x 6” are permitted.</li>


            <li>Opaque oversized bags such as backpacks, tote bags, large purses, camera bags, and similar items will not be permitted inside the venue.</li>


  <li>Accommodations will be made for medically necessary items, diaper bags, and strollers. These items will be subject to inspection.</li> 


  <li>Graduates and faculty and staff participating in the processional will take part in a brief, <strong>no-touch visual search</strong> when entering the lineup area in the West Gym and will need to carry their gowns in with them, putting them on after they’ve completed the screening.</li>
            </ul>
These steps are becoming standard at universities and venues across the country. They’re simple, but they go a long way in helping us create a safe, efficient, and positive environment for our graduates and their families. <strong><a href="https://commencement.humboldt.edu/faq">See the FAQ</a></strong> on the Commencement website for more information.</mj-text>
        <mj-text>
Commencement is such a special day for our students, so thank you for everything you do to make it memorable.
</mj-text>
